race.comment: ABSTRUSE (4) doesn't win often but was eye-catching last start at Moruya, rattling home late. Expect her to be charging again. MELIDESH (3) was plain fresh at Kilmore but is better for the run, draws well, and gets McDougall. Capable of sharp improvement. VAINSTREAM (6) flopped in town but had excuses. Prior form is strong enough to be right in this. PUSSYFOOT (5) looked a run short when resuming with a 2.75 lengths fourth at Dubbo and can only be fitter, expected to go close. FINN'S THE ICON (8) can do better than last start at Wagga Riverside when a disappointing seventh and can contest today.
